DIV1.P:
As the rite of confirmation, is thus sanctioned by the holy scriptures, and the general practice of churches of Christ, in all ages; as it is, in itself, most rational, and calculated to be


productive of very happy effects, we cannot, therefore, but applaud the piety and wisdom of the church of England, at the time of the reformation, in retaining this institution;


after having separated from it, every practice that was offen∣sive, or superstitious.
